.TH NOTEPAD-EXTRA 1 "2026-07-18" "notepad-extra 0.5.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
notepad-extra \- small, fast, fully offline text and code editor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B notepad-extra
.RI [ FILE ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Notepad Extra
is a small, fast, fully offline text and code editor for Windows, macOS and
Linux, built as a native Rust application and inspired by Notepad++.
.PP
It offers tabbed editing, syntax highlighting for over 200 languages with
automatic detection from the file extension, find/replace/go\-to\-line with
regex and case options, word wrap, editor zoom and light/dark themes. A file's
original line endings (LF or CRLF) are preserved on save. The application works
fully offline and makes no network requests.
.PP
Any
.I FILE
arguments are opened in new tabs on startup. Files can also be opened from the
.B Open
dialog or by dragging and dropping them onto the window.
.SH OPTIONS
.B Notepad Extra
takes no command\-line options; non\-option arguments are treated as files to
open.
.SH KEYBOARD SHORTCUTS
.TP
.B Ctrl+N
New tab.
.TP
.B Ctrl+O
Open a file.
.TP
.B Ctrl+S
Save the current file.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+S
Save As.
.TP
.B "Ctrl+Z , Ctrl+Shift+Z , Ctrl+Y"
Undo, and redo (either redo binding).
.TP
.B Ctrl+F
Find.
.TP
.B Ctrl+H
Replace.
.TP
.B F3 ", " Shift+F3
Find next / previous.
.TP
.B Ctrl+G
Go to line.
.TP
.B "Ctrl++ , Ctrl+- , Ctrl+0"
Zoom in, out and reset.
.TP
.B Esc
Dismiss the About panel or the find bar.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/notepad-extra/preferences.json
Editor preferences: theme, word wrap, zoom, the line-number gutter and the chosen
editor and UI fonts. Falls back to
.I ~/.config/notepad-extra/preferences.json
when
.B $XDG_CONFIG_HOME
is unset. Written atomically, and absent until preferences are first saved.
